name: Quorum Meeting - 1.pdf
text:
There is a strong preference for conducting tasks of fline, with suggestions to hold weekend
challenges of fline for those who complete the week's online problems.
Adding timers to increase dif ficulty and handwriting questions to prevent copying.
Proposals were made to use classrooms for of fline monitoring of solutions.
Introducing a system like Nibbler Program with weekly targets.
Pranavv suggested organizing a premiere hackathon event.
Anish's idea was to make the coding problems harder and send them as handwritten images to
discourage cheating. Additionally , block AI sites on the college Wi-Fi. There’ s also a suggestion
to combine aptitude and coding tests, where the result of one leads to the next challenge,
similar to an ARG.
The Extended Council has been dissolved, and discussions will now take place in each lead's
respective group.
There will be no reports for AdHoc meetings.
